## Security & Performance

### Security Measures
- **IP tracking**: Auto-logged for spam prevention
- **Webhook security**: HMAC signature verification required
- **Input validation**: Server-side validation all user inputs  
- **Content moderation**: All proposals require human approval

### Performance Optimizations
- **Map rendering**: SSR disabled, efficient marker management
- **Search**: 700ms debouncing, smart zoom calculation
- **Caching**: Client-side locationStore cache
- **Database**: Spatial indexing on (lat,lng), unique slug index

---

## Troubleshooting Guide

### Map Issues
- **Not loading**: Check SSR disabled, Leaflet CSS loaded, bounds correct
- **Pins missing**: Verify D1 sync, check webhook logs, confirm approved status

### Webhook Problems  
- **Not firing**: Verify URL in Sanity, check secret configuration
- **Sync failures**: Check signature verification, review D1 binding, examine logs

### Build Failures
- **Type errors**: Run `npm run cf-typegen`, check interface exports
- **Test failures**: Review mocks, check API contracts
- **ESLint errors**: Fix any violations, ensure no `any` types

---

## Critical Rules for Code Changes

### ALWAYS Before Committing
1. ✅ **Tests pass**: `npm run test:run` shows 34/34 green
2. ✅ **Lint clean**: `npm run lint` reports no errors  
3. ✅ **Build succeeds**: `npm run check` completes successfully
4. ✅ **Types current**: `npm run cf-typegen` if Cloudflare changes made

### NEVER Do This
- ❌ Use `any` types (ESLint will catch this)
- ❌ Commit failing tests
- ❌ Modify D1 schema without updating both interfaces
- ❌ Skip webhook signature verification
- ❌ Allow direct-to-map posting (bypass moderation)

### Data Integrity Rules
- 🔒 **Only approved pins in D1**: Webhook enforces this rule
- 🔒 **Webhook is source of truth**: For Sanity → D1 sync
- 🔒 **All proposals start pending**: No exceptions
- 🔒 **IP always logged**: For spam prevention

This rule serves as the definitive reference for the complete "Bucureștiul Posibil" system. Consult before making changes to ensure consistency and system integrity.